obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (1417)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995&sectionId=1417&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Seeds Act, 1966.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall came into force on such date`
  line `^1as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint, and different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Act, and`
  line `for different States or for different areas thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 2nd September, 1968,`
  line vide
  line `notification No. S.O.`
  line 3122
  line `, dated`
  line 29
  line `th August, 19`
  line 68
  line `, in respect of ss.`
  line `1 to 6, ss. 8 to 11, s. 18, ss. 22`
  line `to 25`
  line see
  line `Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
  line `1st October, 19`
  line 69,
  line vide
  line `notification No. S.O.`
  line 4049,
  line `dated the`
  line 24th
  line September
  line `, 19`
  line 69,
  line `in respect of`
  line `ss. 7, 12 to 17 (both inclusive)`
  line `and 19 to 21`
  line `(both inclusive),`
  line see
  line `Gazette of India, Extraordinary,`
  line `Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (1418)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 55 of 1972, s. 2 (w.e.f. 16-1-1973).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995&sectionId=1418&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(1) "agriculture" includes horticulture;`
  line
  line `(2) "Central Seed Laboratory" means the Central Seed Laboratory established or declared as such`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(3) "certification agency" means the certification agency established under section 8 or`
  line `recognised under section 18;`
  line
  line `(4) "Committee" means the Central Seed Committee constituted under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 3;`
  line
  line `(5) "container" means a box, bottle, gasket, tin, barrel, case, receptacle, sack, bag, wrapper or`
  line `other thing in which any article or thing is placed or packed;`
  line
  line `(6) "export" means taking out of India to a place outside India;`
  line
  line `(7) "import" means bringing into India from a place outside India;`
  line
  line `(8) "kind" means one or more related species or sub-species of crop plants each individually or`
  line `collectively known by one common name such as cabbage, maize, paddy and wheat;`
  line
  line `(9) "notified kind or variety", in relation to any seed, means any kind or variety thereof notified`
  line `under section 5;`
  line
  line `(10) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(11) "seed" means any of the following classes of seeds used for sowing or planting--`
  line
  line `(i) seed of food crops including edible oil seeds and seeds of fruits and vegetables;`
  line
  line `(ii) cotton seeds;`
  line
  line `(iii) seeds of cattle fodder;`
  line
  line `^2[(iv) jute seeds,]`
  line `and includes seedlings, and tubers, bulbs, rhizomes, roots, cuttings, all types of grafts and other`
  line `vegetatively propagated material, of food crops or cattle fodder;`
  line
  line `(12) "Seed Analyst" means a Seed Analyst appointed under section 12;`
  line
  line `(13) "Seed Inspector" means a Seed Inspector appointed under section 13;`
  line
  line `(14) "State Government" in relation to a Union Territory, means the administrator thereof;`
  line
  line `(15) "State Seed Laboratory", in relation to any State, means the State Seed Laboratory`
  line `established or declared as such under sub-section (2) of section 4 for that State; and`
  line
  line `(16) "variety"means a sub-division of a kind identifiable by growth, yield, plant, fruit, seed, or`
  line `other characteristic.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (1419)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Central Seed Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995&sectionId=1419&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, as soon as may be after the`
  line `commencement of this Act, constitute a Committee called the Central Seed Committee to advice the`
  line `Central Government and the State Governments on matters arising out of the administration of this Act`
  line `and to carry out the other functions assigned to it by or under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Committee shall consist of the following members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) a Chairman to be nominated by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(ii) eight persons to be nominated by the Central Government to represent such interests as that`
  line `Government thinks fit, of whom not less than two persons shall be representatives of growers of seed;`
  line
  line `(iii) one person to be nominated by the Government of each of the States.`
  line
  line `(3) The members of the Committee shall, unless their seals become vacant earlier by resignation,`
  line `death or otherwise, be entitled to hold office for two years and shall be eligible for re-nomination.`
  line
  line `(4) The Committee may, subject to the previous approval of the Central Government, make bye-laws`
  line `fixing the quorum and regulating its own procedure and the conduct of all business to be transacted by it.`
  line
  line `(5) The Committee may appoint one or more sub-committees, consisting wholly of members of the`
  line `Committee or wholly of other persons or partly of members of the Committee and partly of other persons,`
  line `as it thinks fit, for the purpose of discharging such of its functions as may be delegated to such`
  line `sub-committee or sub-committees by the Committee.`
  line
  line `(6) The functions of the Committee or any sub-committee thereof may be exercised notwithstanding`
  line `any vacancy therein.`
  line
  line `(7) The Central Government shall appoint a person to be the secretary of the Committee and shall`
  line `provide the Committee with such clerical and other staff as the Central Government considers necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (1420)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Central Seed Laboratory and State Seed Laboratory.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995&sectionId=1420&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, establish a Central Seed Laboratory or declare any seed laboratory as`
  line `the Central Seed Laboratory to carry out the functions entrusted to the Central Seed Laboratory by or`
  line `under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, establish one or more State`
  line `Seed Laboratories or declare any seed laboratory as the State Seed Laboratory where analysis of seeds of`
  line `any notified kind or variety shall be carried out by Seed Analysts under this Act in the prescribed manner.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (1421)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Power to notify kinds or varieties of seeds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995&sectionId=1421&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `If the Central Government, after consultation with`
  line `the Committee, is of opinion that it is necessary or expedient to regulate the quality of seed of any kind or`
  line `variety to be sold for purposes of agriculture, it may, by notification in the Official Gazette, declare such`
  line `kind or variety to be a notified kind or variety for the purposes of this Act and different kinds or varieties`
  line `may be notified for different States or for different areas thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (1422)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Power to specify minimum limits of germination and purity, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995&sectionId=1422&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government`
  line `may, after consultation with the Committee and by notification in the Official Gazette, specify--`
  line
  line `(a) the minimum limits of germination and purity with respect to any seed of any notified kind or`
  line variety;
  line
  line `(b) the mark or label to indicate that such seed conforms to the minimum limits of germination`
  line `and purity specified under clause (a) and the particulars which such mark or label may contain.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (1423)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Regulation or sale of seeds of notified kinds or varieties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995&sectionId=1423&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `No person shall, himself or by any`
  line `other person on his behalf, carry on the business of selling, keeping for sale, offering to sell, bartering or`
  line `otherwise supplying any seed of any notified kind or variety, unless--`
  line
  line `(a) such seed is identifiable as to its kind or variety;`
  line
  line `(b) such seed conforms to the minimum limits of germination and purity specified under`
  line `clause (a) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(c) the container of such seed bears in the prescribed manner, the mark or label containing the`
  line `correct particulars thereof, specified under clause (b) of section 6; and`
  line
  line `(d) he complies with such other requirements as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (1424)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Certification agency.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995&sectionId=1424&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `The State Government or the Central Government in consultation with the`
  line `State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, establish a ce`
  line `rtificate agency for the State`
  line `to carry out the functions entrusted to the certification agency by or under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8_a:
  sectionId (1425)
  sectionNo 8A
  orderNo 9
  title `The Central Seed Certification Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 55 of 1972, s. 3 (w.e.f. 16 - 1 - 1973).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995&sectionId=1425&sectionno=8A&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995
obj_root_law_sections_8_a_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[8A. The Central Seed Certification Board.--(1) The Central Government shall, by notification in`
  line `the Official Gazette, establish a Central Seed Certification Board (hereinafter referred to as the Board) to`
  line `advise the Central Government and the State Governments on all matters relating to certification, and to`
  line `co-ordinate the functioning of the agencies established under section 8.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board shall consist of the following members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) a Chairman, to be nominated by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(ii) four members, to be nominated by the Central Government from out of the persons employed`
  line `by the State Governments as Directors of Agriculture;`
  line
  line `(iii) three members, to be nominated by the Central Government from out of the persons`
  line `employed by the Agricultural Universities as Directors of Research;`
  line
  line `(iv) thirteen persons, to be nominated by the Central Government to represent such interests as`
  line `that Government thinks fit, of whom not less than four persons shall be representatives of seed`
  line `producers or tradesmen.`
  line
  line `(3) A member of the Board shall, unless his seat becomes vacant earlier by resignation or otherwise,`
  line `be entitled to hold office for two years from the date of his nomination:`
  line
  line `Provided that a person nominated under clause (ii) or clause (iii) of sub-section (2) shall hold office`
  line `only for so long as he holds the appointment by virtue of which his nomination was made.]`
obj_root_law_sections_8_b:
  sectionId (1426)
  sectionNo 8B
  orderNo 10
  title `Other Committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 55 of 1972, s. 3 (w.e.f. 16-1-1973).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995&sectionId=1426&sectionno=8B&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995
obj_root_law_sections_8_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[8B. Other Committees.--The Board may appoint as many Committees as it deems fit consisting`
  line `wholly of the members of the Board or wholly of other persons or partly of members of the Board and`
  line `partly of other persons as it thinks fit to exercise such powers and perform such duties as may be`
  line `delegated to them, subject to such conditions as it may think fit, by the Board.]`
obj_root_law_sections_8_c:
  sectionId (1427)
  sectionNo 8C
  orderNo 11
  title `Proceedings of Board or Committee not to be invalid by reason of any vacancy therein.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 55 of 1972, s. 3 (w.e.f. 16-1-1973).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995&sectionId=1427&sectionno=8C&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995
obj_root_law_sections_8_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[8C. Proceedings of Board or Committee not to be invalid by reason of any vacancy`
  line `therein.--No proceeding of the Board or any Committee thereof shall become invalid merely by reason`
  line `of the existence of any vacancy therein or any defect in the constitution thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_d:
  sectionId (1428)
  sectionNo 8D
  orderNo 12
  title `Procedure for Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_d_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 55 of 1972, s. 3 (w.e.f. 16-1-1973).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995&sectionId=1428&sectionno=8D&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995
obj_root_law_sections_8_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[8D. Procedure for Board.--The Board may, subject to the previous approval of the`
  line `Central Government, make bye-laws for the purpose of regulating its own procedure and the procedure`
  line `of any Committee thereof and the conduct of all business to be transacted by it or such Committee.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_e:
  sectionId (1429)
  sectionNo 8E
  orderNo 13
  title `Secretary and other officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_e_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 55 of 1972, s. 3 (w.e.f. 16-1-1973).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995&sectionId=1429&sectionno=8E&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995
obj_root_law_sections_8_e_content:
  string
  line `^1[8E. Secretary and other officers.--The Central Government shall--`
  line
  line `(i) appoint a person to be the Secretary of the Board, and`
  line
  line `(ii) provide the Board with such technical and other staff as the Central Government considers`
  line necessary.]
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (1430)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 14
  title `Grant of certificate by certification agency.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995&sectionId=1430&sectionno=9&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person selling, keeping for sale, offering`
  line `to sell, bartering or otherwise supplying any seed of any notified kind or variety may, if he desires to have`
  line `such seed certified by the certification agency, apply to the certification agency for the grant of a`
  line `certificate for the purpose.`
  line
  line `(2) Every application under sub-section (1) shall be made in such form, shall contain such particulars`
  line `and shall be accompanied by such fees as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) On receipt of any such application for the grant of a certificate, the certification agency may, after`
  line `such enquiry as it thinks fit and after satisfying itself that the seed to which the application relates`
  line `conforms to the ^1`
  line `[prescribed standards], grant a certificate in such form and on such conditions as may be`
  line `prescribed:`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[Provided that such standards shall not be lower than the minimum limits of germination and purity`
  line `specified for that seed under clause (a) of section 6.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 55 of 1972, s. 4, for certain words (w.e.f. 16-1-1973).`
  line
  line `2. The proviso added by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 16-1-1973)`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (1431)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 15
  title `Revocation of certificate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995&sectionId=1431&sectionno=10&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `If the certification agency is satisfied, either on a reference made to it`
  line `in this behalf or otherwise, that--`
  line
  line `(a) the certificate granted by it under section 9 has been obtained by misrepresentation as to an`
  line `essential fact; or`
  line
  line `(b) the holder of the certificate has, without reasonable cause, failed to comply with the`
  line `conditions subject to which the certificate has been granted or has contravened any of the provisions`
  line `of this Act or the rules made thereunder,`
  line
  line `then, without prejudice to any other penalty to which the holder of the certificate may be liable under this`
  line `Act, the certification agency may, after giving the holder of the certificate an opportunity of showing`
  line `cause, revoke the certificate.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (1432)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 16
  title Appeal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995&sectionId=1432&sectionno=11&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person aggrieved by a decision of a certification agency under section 9 or`
  line `section 10, may within thirty days from the date on which the decision is communicated to him and on`
  line `payment of such fees as may be prescribed, prefer an appeal to such authority as may be specified by the`
  line `State Government in this behalf:`
  line
  line `Provided that the appellate authority may entertain an appeal after the expiry of the said period of`
  line `thirty days if it is satisfied that the appellant was prevented by sufficient cause from filing the appeal in`
  line time.
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of an appeal under sub-section (1), the appellate authority shall, after giving the`
  line `appellate an opportunity of being heard, dispose of the appeal as expeditiously as possible.`
  line
  line `(3) Every order of the appellate authority under this section shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (1433)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 17
  title `Seed Analysts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995&sectionId=1433&sectionno=12&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `The State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoi`
  line `nt such`
  line `persons as it thinks fit, having the prescribed qualifications, to be Seed Analysts and define the areas`
  line `within which they shall exercise jurisdiction.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (1434)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 18
  title `Seed Inspectors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995&sectionId=1434&sectionno=13&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint`
  line `such persons as it thinks fit, having the prescribed qualifications, to be Seed Inspectors and define the`
  line `areas within which they shall exercise jurisdiction.`
  line
  line `(2) Every Seed Inspector shall be deemed to be a public servant within the meaning of section 21 of`
  line `the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860) and shall be officially subordinate to such authority as the State`
  line `Government may specify in this behalf`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (1435)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 19
  title `Powers of Seed Inspector.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995&sectionId=1435&sectionno=14&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Seed Inspector may--`
  line
  line `(a) take samples of any seed in any notified kind or variety from--`
  line
  line `(i) any person selling such seed; or`
  line
  line `(ii) any person who is in the course of conveying, delivering or preparing to deliver such seed`
  line `to a purchaser or a consignee; or`
  line
  line `(iii) a purchaser or a consignee after delivery of such seed to him;`
  line
  line `(b) send such sample for analysis to the Seed Analyst for the area within which such sample has`
  line `been taken;`
  line
  line `(c) enter and search at all reasonable times, with such assistance, if any, as he considers`
  line `necessary, any place in which he has reason to believe that an offence under this Act has been or is`
  line `being committed and order in writing the person in possession of any seed in respect of which the`
  line `offence has been or is being committed, not to dispose of any stock of such seed for a specific period`
  line `not exceeding thirty days or, unless the alleged offence is such that the defect may be removed by the`
  line `possessor of the seed, seize the stock of such seed;`
  line
  line `(d) examine any record, register, document or any other material object found in any place`
  line `mentioned in clause (c) and seize the same if he has reason to believe that if may furnish evidence of`
  line `the commission of an offence punishable under this Act; and`
  line
  line `(e) exercise such other powers as may be necessary for carrying out the purposes of this Act or`
  line `any rule made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any sample of any seed of any notified kind or variety is taken under clause (a) of`
  line `sub-section (1), its cost, calculated at the rate at which such seed is usually sold to the public, shall be`
  line `paid on demand to the person from whom it is taken.`
  line
  line `(3) The power conferred by this section includes power to break-open any container in which any`
  line `seed of any notified kind or variety may be contained or to break-open the door of any premises where`
  line `any such seed may be kept for sale:`
  line
  line `Provided that the power to break-open the door shall be exercised only after the owner or any other`
  line `person in occupation of the premises, if he is present therein, refuses to open the door on being called`
  line `upon to do so.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the Seed Inspector takes any action under clause (a) of sub-section (1), he shall, as far as`
  line `possible, call not less than two persons to be present at the time when such action is taken and take their`
  line `signatures on a memorandum to be prepared in the prescribed form and manner.`
  line
  line `(5) The provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898), shall, so far as may be, apply`
  line `to any search or seizure under this section as they apply to any search or seizure made under the authority`
  line `of a warrant issued under section 98 of the said Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (1436)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 20
  title `Procedure to be followed by Seed Inspectors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995&sectionId=1436&sectionno=15&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever a Seed Inspector intends to take`
  line `sample of any seed of any notified kind or variety or analysis, he shall--`
  line
  line `(a) give notice in writing, then and there, of such intention to the person from whom he intends to`
  line `take sample;`
  line
  line `(b) except in special cases provided by rules made under this Act, take three representative`
  line `samples in the prescribed manner and mark and seal or fasten up each sample in such manner as its`
  line `nature permits.`
  line
  line `(2) When samples of any seed of any notified kind or variety are taken under sub-section (1), the Seed`
  line `Inspector shall--`
  line
  line `(a) deliver one sample to the person from whom it has been taken;`
  line
  line `(b) send in the prescribed manner another sample for analysis to the Seed Analyst for the area`
  line `within which such sample has been taken; and`
  line
  line `(c) retain the remaining sample in the prescribed manner for production in case any legal`
  line `proceedings are taken or for analysis by the Central Seed Laboratory under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 16, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(3) If the person from whom the samples have been taken refuses to accept one of the samples, the`
  line `Seed Inspector shall send intimation to the Seed Analyst of such refusal and thereupon the Seed Analyst`
  line `receiving the sample for analysis shall divide it into two parts and shall seal or fasten up one of those parts`
  line `and shall cause it, either upon receipt of the sample or when he delivers his report, to be delivered to the`
  line `Seed Inspector who shall retain it for production in case legal proceedings are taken.`
  line
  line `(4) Where a Seed Inspector takes any action under clause (c) of sub-section (1) of section 14,--`
  line
  line `(a) he shall use all despatch in ascertaining whether or not the seed contravenes any of the`
  line `provisions of section 7 and if it is ascertained that the seed does not so contravene, forthwith revoke`
  line `the order passed under the said clause or, as the case may be, take such action as may be necessary for`
  line `the return of the stock of the seed seized;`
  line
  line `(b) if he seizes the stock of the seed, he shall, as soon as may be, inform a magistrate and take his`
  line `orders as to the custody thereof;`
  line
  line `(c) without prejudice to the institution of any prosecution, if the alleged offence is such that the`
  line `defect may be removed by the possessor of the seed, he shall, on being satisfied that the defect has`
  line `been so removed, forthwith revoke the order passed under the said clause.`
  line
  line `(5) Where a Seed Inspector seizes any record, register, document or any other material object under`
  line `clause (d) of sub-section (1) of section 14, he shall, as soon as may be, inform a magistrate and take his`
  line `orders as to the custody thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (1437)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 21
  title `Report of Seed Analyst.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995&sectionId=1437&sectionno=16&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Seed Analyst shall, as soon as may be after the receipt of the`
  line `sample under sub-section (2) of section 15, analyse the sample at the State Seed Laboratory and deliver,`
  line `in such form as may be prescribed, one copy of the report of the result of the analysis to the Seed`
  line `Inspector and another copy thereof to the person from whom the sample has been taken.`
  line
  line `(2) After the institution of a prosecution under this Act, the accused vendor or the complainant may,`
  line `on payment of the prescribed fee, make an application to the court for sending any of the samples`
  line `mentioned in clause (a) or clause (c) of sub-section (2) of section 15 to the Central Seed Laboratory for its`
  line `report and on receipt of the application, the court shall first ascertain that the mark and the seal or`
  line `fastening as provided in clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 15 are intact and may then despatch the`
  line `sample under its own seal to the Central Seed Laboratory which shall thereupon send its report to the`
  line `court in the prescribed form within one month from the date of receipt of the sample, specifying the result`
  line `of the analysis.`
  line
  line `(3) The report send by the Central Seed Laboratory under sub-section (2) shall supersede the report`
  line `given by the Seed Analyst under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(4) Where the report sent by the Central Seed Laboratory under sub-section (2) is produced in any`
  line `proceedings under section 19, it shall not be necessary in such proceedings to produce any sample or part`
  line `thereof taken for analysis.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (1438)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 22
  title `Restriction on export and import of seeds of notified kinds or varieties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995&sectionId=1438&sectionno=17&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `No person shall, for`
  line `the purpose of showing or planting by any person (including himself), export or import or cause to be`
  line `exported or imported any seed of any notified kind or variety, unless--`
  line
  line `(a) it conforms to the minimum limits of germination and purity specified for that seed under`
  line `clause (a) of section 6; and`
  line
  line `(b) its container bears, in the prescribed manner, the mark or label with the correct particulars`
  line `thereof specified for that seed under clause (b) of section 6.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (1439)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 23
  title `Recognition of seed certification agencies of foreign countries.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995&sectionId=1439&sectionno=18&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government`
  line `may, on the recommendation of the Committee and by notification in the Official Gazette, recognise any`
  line `seed certification agency established in any foreign country, for the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (1440)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 24
  title Penalty.
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995&sectionId=1440&sectionno=19&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `If any person--`
  line
  line `(a) contravenes any provision of this Act or any rule made thereunder; or`
  line
  line `(b) prevents a Seed Inspector from taking sample under this Act; or`
  line
  line `(c) prevents a Seed Inspector from exercising any other power conferred on him by or under this`
  line Act,
  line
  line `he shall, on conviction, be punishable--`
  line
  line `(i) for the first offence with fine which may extend to five hundred rupees, and`
  line
  line `(ii) in the event of such person having been previously convicted of an offence under this section,`
  line `with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months, or with fine which may extend to one`
  line `thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (1441)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 25
  title `Forfeiture of property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995&sectionId=1441&sectionno=20&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `When any person has been convicted under this Act for the`
  line `contravention of any of the provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder, the seed in respect of`
  line `which the contravention has been committed may be forfeited to the Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (1442)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 26
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995&sectionId=1442&sectionno=21&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a`
  line `company, every person who at the time the offence was committed was in charge of, and was responsible`
  line `to, the company for the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company, shall be deemed`
  line `to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment under this Act if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge and that he`
  line `exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be guilty`
  line `of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of`
  line `individuals; and`
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (1443)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 27
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995&sectionId=1443&sectionno=22&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `Not suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against the Government or any officer of the Government for anything which is in good faith done or`
  line `intended to be done under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (1444)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 28
  title `Power to give directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995&sectionId=1444&sectionno=23&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may give such directions to any State`
  line `Government as may appear to the Central Government to be necessary for carrying into execution in the`
  line `State any of the provisions of this Act or of any rule made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (1445)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 29
  title Exemption.
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995&sectionId=1445&sectionno=24&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Act shall apply to any seed of any notified kind or variety grown by`
  line `a person and sold or delivered by him on his own premises direct to another person for being used by that`
  line `person for the purpose of sowing or planting.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (1446)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 30
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995&sectionId=1446&sectionno=25&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_47_00004_196654_1517807324995
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules to carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the functions of the Committee and the travelling and daily allowances payable to members of`
  line `the Committee and members of any sub-Committee appointed under sub-section (5) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) the functions of the Central Seed Laboratory;`
  line
  line `(c) the functions of a certification agency`
  line
  line `(d) the manner of marking or labelling the container of seed of any notified kind or variety under`
  line `clause (c) of section 7 and under clause (b) of section 17;`
  line
  line `(e) the requirements which may be complied with by a person carrying on the business referred to`
  line `in section 7;`
  line
  line `(f) the form of application for the grant of a certificate under section 9, the particulars it may`
  line `contain, the fees which should accompany it, the form of the certificate and the conditions subject to`
  line `which the certificate may be granted;`
  line
  line `^1[(ff) the standards to which seeds should conform;]`
  line
  line `(g) the form and manner in which and the fee on payment of which an appeal may be preferred`
  line `under section 11 and the procedure to be followed by the appellate authority in disposing of the`
  line appeal;
  line
  line `(h) the qualifications and duties of Seed Analysts and Seed Inspectors;`
  line
  line `(i) the manner in which samples may be taken by the Seed Inspector, the procedure for sending`
  line `such samples to the Seed Analyst or the Central Seed Laboratory and the manner of analysing such`
  line samples;
  line
  line `(j) the form of report of the result of the analysis under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 16 and the fees payable in respect of such report under the said sub-section (2);`
  line
  line `(k) the records to be maintained by a person carrying on the business referred to in section 7 and`
  line `the particulars which such records shall contain; and`
  line
  line `(l) any other matter which is to be or may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this Act shall be laid as soon as may be after it is made, before each House`
  line `of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session`
  line `or ^2[in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the`
  line `session or the successive sessions aforesaid] both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or`
  line `both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, that rule shall, thereafter have effect only in such`
  line `modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 55 of 1972, s. 5 (w.e.f. 16-1-1973).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for certain words (w.e.f. 16-1-1973).`
